# Public marketing site (Next.js)
# Local: run website + portal together: `npm run dev:with-portal` (portal opens in new tab from "Client portal").
# Or run `npm run dev` and separately `npm --prefix law-firm-portal/frontend run dev`.
# Production: root `.env.production` is loaded by Next and by `scripts/run-portal-build.mjs` (VITE_* for embedded portal).
# For secrets on a public repo, use Vercel env vars instead, or use gitignored `.env.production.local` locally.
# Same-domain portal: leave NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL unset; "Client portal" links to /portal/login.
# Override portal origin only if the portal is hosted on a different domain:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL=http://localhost:5173
# Legacy mono proxy: `npm run dev:mono` sets NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL in the script.

# Public /api/cases merge (recommended): commit NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL + NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in `.env.production`
# (anon is public by design) and apply SQL migration `law-firm-portal/supabase/migrations/20260410180000_cases_public_website_anon_read.sql`.
# Local dev: copy `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` + `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` from `.env.production` into gitignored `.env.local`
# so `/api/cases` and `/api/reported-judgments` merge Supabase the same way as Vercel.
# Optional legacy fallback (server-only; do not commit): SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in `.env.local`.
# Recommended for /judgments PDFs: same key lets `/api/judgments/pdf` stream files even before the bucket is public; create bucket via migration `20260426180000_storage_reportedjudgements_bucket.sql` then run `node scripts/upload-to-supabase.js`.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
# Reported judgments: same keys let `/api/reported-judgments` merge portal rows from `reported_judgments` over `public/data/reported-judgments.json`.
# Portal → website “Load from website API”: Next allows `http://localhost:5173` in dev; set NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL or FRONTEND_ORIGIN for other origins.
